children.name: cvs_mdrate_county
children.description:
Domain: General Health

Active non-federal physicians (MD's and DO's) in primary care (residents and those 75+ in age excluded) per 100,000 population in county.

What is the supply of MD's and DO's in each county. This measure captures all physicians including those providing primary as well as specialty care. It is important to note that in large counties with one or a few towns or cities, and large rural areas, this value may not represent the accessibility to physician medical care in rural areas.  There may appear to be sufficient numbers of physicians per capita, but they may be geographically distant from rural portions of the county.

children.name: cvs_pctnoins_fem_tract
children.description:
Domain: General Health

Percent of women <65 without health insurance in census tract.

This indicator combines those insured by private and public insurance and focuses on the population not eligible for Medicare. Higher proportions of uninsured suggests potential barriers to accessing primary and specialist care.

children.name: cvs_pctnovehicle_county
children.description:
Domain: Transportation

Percent of households with no vehicles available for use in county.

Households may not have a car because they live in high-density urban areas served by high quality public transportation. But in many communities, public transit is not adequate. This indicator is measured specifically at the neighborhood or census tract level.

children.prompt: Household, no car % in census tract
children.name: cvs_pctnovehicle_tract
children.description:
Domain: Transportation

Percent of households with no vehicles available for use in census tract.

Households may not have a car because they live in high-density urban areas served by high quality public transportation. But in many communities, public transit is not adequate. This indicator is measured specifically at the neighborhood or census tract level.

children.name: cvs_pctmove_tract
children.description:
Domain: Social Support

Percent of households who moved to current residence within past year in census tract.

Communities with stable residents may have enhanced networks and social ties that promote mutual aid and collective action. In contrast communities with high proportions of residential turnover may have barriers to collective community support and action to address shared challenges.

children.prompt: Single parent household % in census tract
children.name: cvs_pctsphh_tract
children.description:
Domain: Social Support

Percent of households with children under 18 headed by single parent in census tract.

Individual families led by a single parent can range from low to high socioeconomic status. However, in general, communities with very high proportion of single parent headed households tend to have increased stress and reduced resilience in response to housing instability, health problems, or loss of employment.

children.name: cvs_pctovercrowdhh_tract
children.description:
Domain: Housing

Percent of households with >1 person per room in census tract.

Communities with high proportion of households categorized as "overcrowded" may reflect housing instability in census tract.

children.name: cvs_pctowner_occ_tract
children.description:
Domain: Housing

Percent of households occupied by owners in census tract.

Home ownership is the primary source of wealth and reflects and important buffer against health or economic stressors.

children.name: cvs_pct_less_well_tract
children.description:
Domain: Neighborhood social stability

Percent of people who speak English "less than very well" in census tract.

Neighborhoods with higher proportion of non-English speakers may indicate the need for adequate translation services in health and social service environments.

children.prompt: Neighborhood Deprivation Index in census tract
children.name: cvs_ndi_raw_tract
children.description:
Domain: Socioeconomic

Composite index of 8 measures of material resources or wealth in census tract.

Neighborhood deprivation is a composite index of measures that proxy economic resources. This index is more general than just the poverty rate or median household income, instead combining multiple other dimensions of socioeconomic resources. Neighborhood deprivation has been associated with a wide variety of maternal and perinatal health outcomes.

children.name: cvs_pctpov_tract
children.description:
Domain: Socioeconomic

Percent of population with income below the federal poverty level in census tract.

The proportion of residents living below the federal poverty line is one of the most robust indicators of higher health burdens. This may partly reflect individual level economic resources to access health relevant resources, but places characterized by high poverty rates may also experience contextual stressors and barriers independent of individual level income.

children.name: cvs_ice_income_all_tract
children.description:
Domain: Socioeconomic

Index of Concentration at Extremes highlighting the spatial concentration and separation of poor and affluent in census tract.

Poverty concentration is measured with the Index of Concentration at the Extremes (ICE), which measures income segregation. Specifically, it goes beyond simply describing the proportion of low-income households, instead focusing on the spatial concentration of affluent households on the one hand and poor households on the other.

children.name: cvs_pctobese_county
children.description:
Domain: General Health

Percent of adults 18+ with BMI >30, estimated with statistical modeling from BRFSS in county.

Unlike individual-level BMI or obesity status, the county prevalence of obesity has been associated with socioeconomic insecurity, as well as lower quality food and physical activity environments and opportunities.

children.name: cvs_fi_county
children.description:
Domain: General Health

Percent of population meeting USDA definition for food insecure, estimated with statistical modeling from state level CPS data in county.

Family-level food insecurity reflects not only expendable income, but also competing expense burdens and support of dependents. At an aggregate level, the prevalence of food insecurity may suggest the intersection of socioeconomic stress with an inadequate safety net to meet basic needs.

children.prompt: Nurse midwives per capita in county
children.name: cvs_cnmrate_county
children.description:
Domain: Reproductive Health

Nurse midwives (CNM and Advanced Practice Nurse midwives) per 100,000 population in county.

Access to certified and advanced practice nurse midwives represent another part of the reproductive health landscape. As noted with other provider-indicators, this indicator could be misleading as a proxy for the accessibility of health providers in a large county with an urbanized area perhaps geographically distant from rural populations.

children.name: cvs_obgynrate_county
children.description:
Domain: Reproductive Health

Active non-federal OB/GYN's in patient care per 100,000 population in county.

Access to general, as well as specialist, obstetric professionals is important. As noted with Physician's per capita (above), this number may be deceiving in some rural counties with a single large town. There may appear to be sufficient numbers of obstetricians per capita, but they may be geographically distant from rural portions of the county.

children.name: cvs_rtteenbirth_county
children.description:
Domain: Reproductive Health

Live births per 1,000 females 15-19; estimates are pooled over several consecutive years in county.

Teen birth rate reflects the intersection of availability and accessibility of sexual health education, family planning, and socioeconomic status. This indicator is included because a county with a high teen birth rate may also experience challenges with other aspects of equitable sexual and reproductive health services.

children.name: cvs_rtstd_county
children.description:
Domain: Reproductive Health

Number of chlamydia cases per 100,000 population in county.

Chlamydia is one of the most common sexually transmitted infection. Because it is preventable through education and access to barrier contraceptives, it is included as a proxy of the reproductive health burden experienced by the population in a given county.

children.name: cvs_rtdrugodmortality_county
children.description:
Domain: Behavioral Health

Drug poisoning deaths per 100,000 population; estimates pooled over several consecutive years in county.

County level drug overdose represents the intersection of substance use disorder, unmet substance use treatment services, and community education and support for substance use and for emergency overdose response.

children.prompt: Social assoc's per capita in county
children.name: cvs_rtsocassoc_county
children.description:
Domain: Social Support

Number of member associations per 10,000 population in county.

An alternative indicator of social capital is the ratio of social member associations per capita. These kinds of associations include civic, social, and religious organizations and may be important for social support, building social networks, and collective action to health and social challenges.

children.name: cvs_pcthouse_distress_county
children.description:
Domain: Housing

Percent of households with at least one of four severe housing problems; estimates are pooled over several consecutive years

Housing distress includes overcrowding, high housing costs, lack of kitchen facilities, or lack of plumbing facilities. High prevalence of housing distress suggests discordance between housing stock and population resources and may be associated with environmental risk from household infrastructure as well as housing instability.

children.name: cvs_rtviolentcr_icpsr_county
children.description:
Domain: Neighborhood social stability

Number of reported violent crime offenses per 100,000 population; estimates are pooled over several consecutive years in county.

Violent crime is risky for individuals involved in the crime, but place-based violent crime may represent a source of stress even to those not directly affected. High violent crime can undermine social stability and sense of safety.

children.name: cvs_isolation_county
children.description:
Domain: Neighborhood social stability

Racial residential dissimilarity segregation index in county.

Residential segregation is an indicator of historical as well as contemporary structural inequalities and spatial stratification. High levels of racial segregation have been associated with a wide range of health outcomes in part because segregation itself produces patterns in neighborhood resources including education, economic opportunity, policing, and social and economic mobility.
